## Code Review Checklist

### Architecture
- [ ] Write path is non-blocking and returns immediately
- [ ] Read path uses SSE, not HTTP polling
- [ ] Message broker is used for fanout, not direct connections
- [ ] Database schema uses composite key (stream_id + timestamp)
- [ ] Regional deployment is considered

### Performance
- [ ] No blocking I/O on critical path
- [ ] Message batching is implemented
- [ ] Connection limits per gateway are defined
- [ ] Database queries use partition key
- [ ] Caching strategy is defined (if applicable)

### Reliability
- [ ] Graceful degradation on Redis failure
- [ ] SSE auto-reconnect is handled
- [ ] Rate limiting is implemented
- [ ] Circuit breakers are in place
- [ ] Dead letter queue for failed messages

### Observability
- [ ] Metrics are emitted (latency, throughput, errors)
- [ ] Distributed tracing is added
- [ ] Structured logging is used
- [ ] Health check endpoints exist
- [ ] Alerting thresholds are defined

